===Alternative forms===
* In Japanese {{w|shinjitai}}, the bottom component is simplified to {{m|mul|大}}, rather than the traditional {{m|mul|犬||dog|sc=Hani}}.
** This character has technically been encoded in Unicode as {{m|mul|𦤀}} (<code>U+26900</code>) but is not used in Japanese computing; instead, the character {{m|mul|臭}} (<code>U+81ED</code>) changes appearance depending on the font.
** A {{w|CJK Compatibility Ideographs|CJK compatibility ideograph}} exists at <code>U+FA5C</code> for the {{w|kyūjitai}} form used in Japanese which contains {{l|mul|犬}} as its bottom component.

